{"_type":"issue","id":"switchboard-u7y","title":"Learning loop: decision notes + pattern surfacing in sw done/resume","description":"Add a lightweight learning loop to sw done and sw resume.\n\nsw done: add --decision/-D flag for a short freeform note capturing the non-obvious insight that unblocked the jack (what was hard, what was the key decision). Store this as a first-class Qdrant field alongside commit_msg and diff_summary.\n\nsw resume: surface 2-3 semantically similar past jacks alongside the TSO, showing their decision notes. This gives the agent picking up a jack immediate access to 'here is what worked last time on similar work.'\n\nInspired by Ruflo's RETRIEVE-\u003eJUDGE-\u003eDISTILL-\u003eCONSOLIDATE-\u003eROUTE loop, but scoped to our 1-3 agent use case — no swarm machinery needed. The value is in the decision note being required on closure, not in routing complexity.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"cleoOpenClaw@proton.me","created_at":"2026-04-29T21:57:20Z","created_by":"Cleo","updated_at":"2026-04-29T21:57:20Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
